# Role Access Hierarchy

When gating modules or functionality by role permissions, follow this **implicit grant chain**. Do not require each tier to be checked manually in every feature.

## Default rules

1. **Administrator (`role_id = 1`)** — unrestricted access to everything. Never duplicate Admin checks beyond the shared helpers.
2. **Top Management Access** — any feature gated on `Top Management Access` must also allow **Administrator**.
3. **Sr Emp Access** — any feature gated on `Sr Emp Access` must also allow **Top Management Access** and **Administrator**.

## Hierarchy (lowest → highest privilege for gating)

```
Sr Emp Access  →  Top Management Access  →  Administrator (unrestricted)
```

## Implementation (required)

Use helpers in `helpers/html_helpers.php` — do **not** hand-roll permission checks in controllers/views:

| Helper | Use when |
|--------|----------|
| `isAdministratorUser()` | Admin-only bypass |
| `hasTieredAccess($userId, $minimumAccess, $moduleNames)` | Feature needs Sr Emp or Top Management tier |
| `hasTieredModuleAccess($userId, $module, $minimumAccess)` | Single module check |
| `canSrEmpAccess()` | Sr Emp–level POS/order admin actions (includes Top Management + Admin) |

```php
// ✅ Sr Emp–gated feature (Top Management + Admin included automatically)
if (!hasTieredAccess((int)($_SESSION['user']['id'] ?? 0), 'Sr Emp Access')) {
    vendorJsonResponse(['success' => false, 'message' => 'Access denied.']);
}

// ✅ Top Management–gated feature (Admin included automatically)
if (!hasTieredAccess((int)($_SESSION['user']['id'] ?? 0), 'Top Management Access', ['Reports'])) {
    exit;
}

// ❌ BAD — omits Top Management / Admin implicit grants
if (!hasPermission($userId, 'POS Orders', 'Sr Emp Access')) { ... }
```

## Views

Pass a boolean from the presenter (e.g. `canEditOrderNumber => canSrEmpAccess()`) or call tiered helpers in the view only when the presenter already validated the pattern. Never show Admin-only UI without the helper chain.

## New permissions

When adding a new access tier to `vp_role_access`, document where it sits in the hierarchy and extend `getAccessTiersIncluding()` in `html_helpers.php` if it sits between existing tiers.
